the function read_file is
  given a path of text, returns the file contents as text.
  requires the path is within the allowed workspace root.
  ensures the contents reflect the file at the time of the read.

the function write_file is
  given a path of text and contents of text, returns yes or no.
  requires the path is within the allowed workspace root.
  requires the contents are valid utf-8 text.
  ensures the file at the path matches the contents after the call returns yes.

the function list_dir is
  given a path of text, returns a list of file names as text.
  requires the path is a directory within the allowed workspace root.
  ensures the listing excludes hidden files unless explicitly requested.
